{"change_summary":"Replaced fragile comma-delimited completion journal details with structured JSON rendering in `milestone_record`, kept backward-compatible legacy parsing in the filesystem adapter, and taught completion replay to rewrite malformed legacy completion events in place when backfilling metadata. Also canonicalized direct `append_task_run` writes so every newly appended NDJSON row persists the explicit `milestone_id`, then added regressions for delimiter-containing identifiers, legacy journal repair, JSON detail rendering, and raw on-disk milestone_id persistence.","outstanding_risks":["Milestone mutations still span separate lineage, snapshot, and journal files without a cross-file transaction, so a crash between file writes can still leave snapshot or journal state temporarily behind `task-runs.ndjson` until the same operation is replayed or state is reconciled from lineage."],"steps":[{"description":"Updated completion-detail rendering in `src/contexts/milestone_record/model.rs` to emit structured JSON payloads that safely preserve `project_id`, `run_id`, and `plan_hash` even when they contain delimiter text, and added a model regression covering those identifiers.","order":0,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Extended `src/adapters/fs.rs` so completion journal repair parses both new JSON payloads and legacy delimited strings, rewrites malformed legacy completion events to the canonical structured form during replay, and forces `milestone_id` onto any row written through `append_task_run`.","order":1,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Expanded `src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs` regressions to verify raw `task-runs.ndjson` persistence of `milestone_id`, JSON completion details on replay, and repair of a legacy malformed completion journal event without creating duplicates, then revalidated formatting, milestone-record tests, and clippy.","order":2,"status":"completed"}],"validation_evidence":["`cargo fmt --all` completed successfully.","`cargo test --lib contexts::milestone_record` passed with 86 tests.","`cargo clippy -- -D warnings` completed successfully."]}